BBC 3 HD 15th Nov 2014
7:30pm to 8:30pm Highlights

Jason Mohammad introduces the best action and reaction from England's clash against South Africa at Twickenham. Having faced world champions New Zealand the previous weekend, Stuart Lancaster's England can expect another formidable test against the Springboks. Heyneke Meyer's side ended New Zealand's 22-match unbeaten run in October, and they have not lost to England in their last 11 meetings. The most recent was particularly chastening for England, who lost 16-15 at Twickenham two years ago after opting to kick a late penalty rather than go for the try that would have put them in front. Commentary by Alistair Bruce-Ball and Brian Moore with analysis from England World Cup-winner Lewis Moody.
